Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharpish turn. Clay fine pink-brown. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Name Leontidas. Trimmed. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0168.24.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1120)
